Hehehe, thats funny. I must be doing something right since no one has done this to me.<br>
<br>
One of the bad things being a mage is that fact that your stupid pile of earth/air/water/fire is going to automatically agro on any mob that hits you, regardless of whether it is the one the puller is on.<br>
I cant remember the number of time ive assisted on the puller and sic'd the pet onto the mob, only to take a single hit from a mob that has just had its mez wear off and have the pet jump straight on it, making life soooo much harder for the enchanter till Ive mashed my &quot;Pet Backoff&quot; key through my keyboard and desk.<br>
The fact our pets do this is one of the primary things the mage community @ magecompendium.com are trying to get VI to fix, hopefully by way of a new pet command that will not make the pet agro on a mob thats whacking us.<br>
<br>
Just a question about the first post/rant.<br>
Lotsa valid points about high lvl players who know jack and I think the rant is warranted, but do you react this way when grouped with the people or are you more inclined to go out of your way and suggest to them what they can do to play better?<br>
I cant say that I take the time, it depends on my mood. Once grouped with a 30 something enchanter who didnt know what a mez was. I was really inclined to boot them from the group at that point, no warning. Be afraid of an enchanter that doesnt know what a mez is. <p>cheers<BR>
